abstract: Swedish prosecutors drop cases of lesser sexual misconduct against WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange but still want to question him on rape accusations made after his visit to Stockholm in 2010.
lead_paragraph: Swedish prosecutors on Thursday dropped cases of lesser sexual misconduct against WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange but said they still want to question him on accusations of rape made after his visit to Stockholm five years ago.

headline.main: Sweden Drops Some Sex Cases Against Assange
headline.print_headline: World Briefing | Europe; Sweden: Prosecutors Drop 3 Cases Against Assange
